The 1921 application was purchased by Delaware rare book dealer Ian Brabner .
It asks 'are you of the white race or of a colored race?'
It also asks 'do you believe in the principles of a PURE Americanism?'
The form is ominously titled ‘Invisible Empire’, an alternative name for the clan at the time, born from founder Nathan Bedford Forrest’s claim that the group was ‘invisible’